Map=(MapName="DH-Stoumont_Advance",Acronym=DH,PlayerCountMin=32,PlayerCountMax=64,FriendlyName=DH-Stoumont_Advance.LevelSummary.Title,Author="Darklight Games",ScreenShot=DH-Stoumont_Advance.Previews.Stomount3,Description=DH-Stoumont_Advance.LevelSummary.Description,FallbackDesc="19th December, 1944||In the initial phase of the Battle of the Bulge, Kampfgruppe Peiper attacked toward Bastogne through La Gleize to Stoumont using heavy Panzers and mechanized Infantry to strike US troops that had been told the Ardennes would be a rest area.||The near total absence of air support for the Allies would allow the last large and well-equipped units of the Wehrmacht and SS to advance in the style that had brought them victory many times before.||But, any kind of weather can only last so long. Wherever the US soldiers had armor support or artillery, the proper use of them would spell the difference between survival and annihilation.",FallbackName="Stoumont")